	abstract = {SPARKLIS is a Semantic Web tool that helps users explore and query SPARQL endpoints by guiding them in the interactive building of questions and answers, from simple ones to complex ones. It combines the ﬁne-grained guidance of faceted search, most of the expressivity of SPARQL, and the readability of (controlled) natural languages. No knowledge of the vocabulary and schema are required for users. Many SPARQL features are covered: multidimensional queries, union, negation, optional, ﬁlters, aggregations, ordering. Queries are verbalized in either English or French, so that no knowledge of SPARQL is ever necessary. All of this is implemented in a portable Web application, SPARKLIS, and has been evaluated on many endpoints and questions. No endpoint-speciﬁc conﬁguration is necessary as the data schema is discovered on the ﬂy by the tool. Online since April 2014, thousands of queries have been formed by hundreds of users over hundreds of endpoints.},
